function keep_only_names(words)
    return filter(word -> startswith(uppercase(word), "A") || startswith(uppercase(word), "E") || startswith(uppercase(word), "I") || startswith(uppercase(word), "O") || startswith(uppercase(word), "U"), words)
end
```
This function uses the `filter` function to iterate over each word in the list and check if it starts with a capital letter. If it does, then we keep it in the output list. Otherwise, we remove it. We use `startswith` to check if the word starts with a certain letter and `uppercase` to convert the word to uppercase before checking.
